jg@opal.cs.uow.edu.au (Jonathon Giddy) writes:
>I am an Honours student in Computer Science, wishing to tap the 
>combined knowledge of the 'Net. I am looking for references
>to stuff to do with automatic cryptanalysis of simple ciphers.

You should lookup the folllowing article, and contact her supervisor
Prof Carroll, in Dept Computer Science, University of Western Ontario,
London, Ontario, Canada N6A 5B7.
as he has continued his work since.

Lynda Robbins, "The Automated Cryptanalysis of Polyalphabetic Ciphers",
Cryptologia 11(4) Oct 1987 pp193-205.

John m Carroll, Lynda Robbins, "Computer Cryptanalysis",
Technical Report 223, Dec 1988, 55pp, Dept Computer Science,
Uni Western Ontario.

Good luck.
Cheers
Dr Lawrie Brown

